Well, I already told you.

526
00:33:34,740 --> 00:33:41,156
I have your back.
So don't worry about anything.

527
00:33:41,156 --> 00:33:46,505
If anyone bothers you,
I'll bite off his nose!

528
00:33:46,505 --> 00:33:49,388
Wow, I feel stronger now.

529
00:33:50,421 --> 00:33:52,267
Cheer up, Yoon Tae Soo!

530
00:33:52,827 --> 00:33:55,055
Cheer up, Kim Eun Ok!

531
00:33:57,829 --> 00:34:01,306
<i>Let's go through the jungle.</i>

532
00:34:01,306 --> 00:34:05,705
<i>Let's crawl through the jungle.</i>

533
00:34:06,234 --> 00:34:10,047
<i>When you see a "swap"</i>

534
00:34:10,047 --> 00:34:12,938
<i>You'll see crocodiles!</i>

535
00:34:12,938 --> 00:34:14,786
<i>Crocodiles!</i>

536
00:34:21,266 --> 00:34:23,626
Smells good.

537
00:34:27,773 --> 00:34:29,545
Cheer up!

538
00:34:53,115 --> 00:34:54,768
What is it?

539
00:34:54,768 --> 00:34:57,936
Oh... it's nothing.

540
00:34:57,936 --> 00:34:59,554
Are we already home?

541
00:34:59,554 --> 00:35:02,811
No. Sleep more.

542
00:35:37,362 --> 00:35:43,027
I will close my speech with a proverb
that I've been cherishing in my heart.

543
00:35:43,027 --> 00:35:44,773
Put it into action!

544
00:35:44,773 --> 00:35:47,931
Your dream comes true when
you put them into action!

545
00:35:48,570 --> 00:35:50,894
Gorgeous. Gorgeous.

546
00:35:52,418 --> 00:35:56,436
That was an impressive candidacy speech.

547
00:35:59,751 --> 00:36:03,454
Is there anyone else who wants
to run in the election?

548
00:36:03,454 --> 00:36:05,492
I'm sure there isn't anyone.

549
00:36:05,492 --> 00:36:07,273
Then...

550
00:36:07,273 --> 00:36:11,764
Lee Do Kyung is the sole candidate
for the chairwoman position--

551
00:36:11,764 --> 00:36:13,452
Wait a moment.

552
00:36:13,452 --> 00:36:15,581
I would like to run for the election too.

553
00:36:17,862 --> 00:36:19,657
You would, Eun Ok?

554
00:36:22,105 --> 00:36:24,820
Then, why don't you give us a speech too?

555
00:36:36,146 --> 00:36:40,592
For the past five years,
since the birth of One Heart...

556
00:36:40,592 --> 00:36:43,199
I was the Chairwoman of One Heart.

557
00:36:43,199 --> 00:36:48,750
I had praises. I also made many mistakes.

558
00:36:48,750 --> 00:36:52,760
I know I'm lacking.

559
00:36:52,760 --> 00:36:55,943
That's why I thought of stepping down.

560
00:36:55,943 --> 00:37:00,199
However, after some serious thinking,
I came to a conclusion.

561
00:37:00,199 --> 00:37:03,503
No parents would give up their children.

562
00:37:03,503 --> 00:37:06,920
Just like that,
I can't give up One Heart.

563
00:37:12,277 --> 00:37:14,826
More than anything, I believe...

564
00:37:14,826 --> 00:37:20,400
The members of One Heart will not
be blown away by a cosmetics gift set.

565
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:23,440
That's what I want to prove.

566
00:37:26,802 --> 00:37:30,349
Then... according to the order
of candidacy submission...

567
00:37:30,349 --> 00:37:35,199
Candidate number one, Lee Do Kyung!

568
00:37:35,199 --> 00:37:37,456
Number two, Kim Eun Ok.

569
00:37:38,273 --> 00:37:42,304
The election is in three days.

570
00:37:42,304 --> 00:37:46,056
We'll have a new chairwoman then.

571
00:37:47,284 --> 00:37:52,266
Wow, Director Baek! Congratulations!

572
00:37:52,789 --> 00:37:55,132
Wow, you came to visit us yourself.

573
00:37:55,132 --> 00:37:57,983
I don't need that kind of thing.
Put it outside. Outside, outside!

574
00:37:57,983 --> 00:38:00,664
Now you are the CEO of a
movie production company!

575
00:38:00,664 --> 00:38:03,742
How can I just sit around doing nothing?

576
00:38:03,742 --> 00:38:07,570
These are the people who will
make you a billionaire, like me!

577
00:38:07,570 --> 00:38:09,782
Nice to meet you!

578
00:38:13,010 --> 00:38:14,719
What are you doing here?

579
00:38:15,643 --> 00:38:16,972
Hold on, Tae Soo.

580
00:38:16,972 --> 00:38:20,746
Director Cho came to congratulate us.
He also introduced us to an investor.

581
00:38:21,588 --> 00:38:23,135
Are you crazy?

582
00:38:23,748 --> 00:38:26,353
How can you let just anyone in here?

583
00:38:26,353 --> 00:38:29,306
Well, Director Yoon.

584
00:38:29,306 --> 00:38:33,030
Long time, no see. I've missed you.

585
00:38:34,586 --> 00:38:37,195
What did I say would happen
if we ever saw each other?

586
00:38:38,335 --> 00:38:39,545
Huh?

587
00:38:39,545 --> 00:38:42,465
Geez, I forgot.

588
00:38:42,465 --> 00:38:45,686
Please understand. I'm an idiot.

589
00:38:45,686 --> 00:38:49,175
This idiot is going home then.

590
00:38:58,056 --> 00:39:01,550
What was that?
That was my guest.

591
00:39:02,818 --> 00:39:05,219
He's a swindler, not a guest.

592
00:39:05,219 --> 00:39:08,945
If he came to invest,
he's our guest, no matter what he is!

593
00:39:10,614 --> 00:39:14,840
Be careful, Tae Soo.
You are going to be full of regret.

594
00:39:22,318 --> 00:39:24,577
Who's that guy next to Gi Bum?

595
00:39:24,577 --> 00:39:27,197
He's Director Cho Dong Choon,
from Gunseol Group.

596
00:39:27,197 --> 00:39:29,175
What the heck...

597
00:39:29,175 --> 00:39:32,291
Do you want to make a movie or not?

598
00:39:32,291 --> 00:39:36,110
Questionable people come and go
all the time, and they say nonsense!

599
00:39:36,110 --> 00:39:39,264
He looks like a gangster’s errand boy.

600
00:39:41,454 --> 00:39:45,130
You were happy to death when he gave
you the car keys and the credit card.

601
00:39:45,130 --> 00:39:47,744
Now you've come to your senses?

602
00:39:52,226 --> 00:39:54,918
What brings you here, Mr. Chairman?

603
00:39:59,072 --> 00:40:01,822
Why did Cho Dong Choon come here?

604
00:40:03,679 --> 00:40:05,777
He came to see Gi Bum.

605
00:40:05,777 --> 00:40:07,800
What are you doing, Tae Soo?

606
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:11,721
If Gi Bum does something wrong,
you should stop him!

607
00:40:11,721 --> 00:40:13,934
How could you allow that?

608
00:40:13,934 --> 00:40:17,000
Is this how you handle things?

609
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:20,153
How can I trust you with anything?

610
00:40:23,650 --> 00:40:27,172
You didn't trust me with
the movie entirely.

611
00:40:29,596 --> 00:40:33,240
Are you... blaming me now?

612
00:40:42,697 --> 00:40:44,101
Tae Soo.

613
00:40:45,119 --> 00:40:50,378
Now that I see you today,
you sit really tall, yeah?

614
00:40:50,378 --> 00:40:52,418
You are even taller than I am!

615
00:41:11,358 --> 00:41:16,710
Let's have an election that is
clean, honorable, and free of bribery.

616
00:41:16,710 --> 00:41:19,552
Just like the color white,
which represents One Heart.

617
00:41:19,552 --> 00:41:23,384
In particular, do not spread lies
about a candidate's past.

618
00:41:23,384 --> 00:41:26,914
My strategy is to be mysterious.

619
00:41:26,914 --> 00:41:28,903
Just like the color purple.

620
00:41:32,469 --> 00:41:35,989
Candidates, your eyes
are quite scary right now.

621
00:41:35,989 --> 00:41:41,083
A clean election starts with... a smile!

622
00:41:41,083 --> 00:41:43,987
Oh, Madam asked me
to take pictures of you.

623
00:41:43,987 --> 00:41:47,487
Please come forward and shake
hands with each other.

624
00:41:51,987 --> 00:41:53,483
Okay.

625
00:41:58,346 --> 00:42:00,608
Okay. Ready...

626
00:42:00,608 --> 00:42:03,286
Please shake hands.

627
00:42:04,028 --> 00:42:05,414
Shake hands.

628
00:42:06,474 --> 00:42:09,885
Smile... one, two, three!

629
00:42:15,365 --> 00:42:17,775
I'm over here.

630
00:42:17,775 --> 00:42:20,436
What is this place?

631
00:42:20,436 --> 00:42:22,981
Why do you ask when you already know?

632
00:42:22,981 --> 00:42:27,085
By the way, did you clean
it up for a guest?

633
00:42:27,085 --> 00:42:29,952
Or did you clean it up to hide something?

634
00:42:29,952 --> 00:42:32,764
You may not know,
since it's Gi Bum's hideout.

635
00:42:32,764 --> 00:42:35,434
Geez, there you go again.

636
00:42:35,434 --> 00:42:37,965
Say it in a way that I can understand.

637
00:42:37,965 --> 00:42:42,905
I believe there's something
between you, Gi Bum and Mr. Son.

638
00:42:42,905 --> 00:42:46,280
Here, Baek Gi Bum was...

639
00:42:49,181 --> 00:42:52,840
Someone reported that he
worked on Mr. Son here.

640
00:42:54,521 --> 00:42:59,262
I should have had forensics work on it.

641
00:42:59,820 --> 00:43:02,603
Then I would have
already gotten a gift box.

642
00:43:03,380 --> 00:43:05,561
What do you think?

643
00:43:05,561 --> 00:43:07,496
Think about what?

644
00:43:07,496 --> 00:43:11,130
Then bring Baek Gi Bum here and ask him!

645
00:43:11,130 --> 00:43:16,315
That brat has his almighty dad
in his back pocket. How can I do that?

646
00:43:17,661 --> 00:43:21,210
What I need is a witness.

647
00:43:24,231 --> 00:43:28,170
Bro, what am I, a woman's heart?

648
00:43:28,170 --> 00:43:30,273
Stop trying to look into it.

649
00:43:30,273 --> 00:43:34,170
You better bring me evidence!

650
00:43:34,170 --> 00:43:35,746
Okay?

651
00:43:36,800 --> 00:43:38,849
I'm a busy man.

652
00:43:38,849 --> 00:43:42,110
Don't trust Baek Man Bo and Baek Gi Bum!

653
00:43:43,579 --> 00:43:48,570
Lots of loyal dogs like you
have gone to jail for them.

654
00:43:49,114 --> 00:43:52,773
I'm worried you might end up like that.

655
00:44:18,628 --> 00:44:20,219
Dad!

656
00:44:21,983 --> 00:44:23,356
What are you listening to?

657
00:44:30,351 --> 00:44:33,670
Wow, what a beautiful voice.

658
00:44:35,811 --> 00:44:39,144
Why don't you listen at home?
It's cold.

659
00:44:40,865 --> 00:44:43,000
Is it because of Mom?

660
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:45,793
You haven't decided yet?

661
00:44:47,014 --> 00:44:48,965
My head is spinning.

662
00:44:51,652 --> 00:44:53,182
Geez.

663
00:44:53,182 --> 00:44:57,376
My head is about to explode too.

664
00:44:59,253 --> 00:45:02,898
Cold air is the best thing
at times like these.

665
00:45:04,284 --> 00:45:08,032
Should we keep taking in this cold air
and just freeze to death?

666
00:45:12,746 --> 00:45:14,143
Okay.

667
00:45:33,155 --> 00:45:34,945
Nonprofit foundation?

668
00:45:34,945 --> 00:45:37,815
Yes, a nonprofit foundation.

669
00:45:37,815 --> 00:45:42,092
That's slight overkill.
We're just a group of volunteers--

670
00:45:42,092 --> 00:45:46,949
That kind of mindset kept One Heart
from growing in the past five years.

671
00:45:46,949 --> 00:45:48,755
What's your point?

672
00:45:48,795 --> 00:45:50,487
Think about it.

673
00:45:50,487 --> 00:45:53,010
It's hard to make a living these days.

674
00:45:53,010 --> 00:45:57,543
We can help the members
buy a house with a loan.

675
00:45:57,543 --> 00:46:02,530
And for families with kids in schools,
we can set up scholarship funds.

676
00:46:02,530 --> 00:46:06,625
Helping others is all well and good.

677
00:46:06,625 --> 00:46:11,181
However, the real growth should start
with benefiting our own members.

678
00:46:11,181 --> 00:46:16,338
Wow, why haven't we ever thought of that?

679
00:46:16,338 --> 00:46:20,150
Do Kyung, that is a great idea!

680
00:46:20,150 --> 00:46:24,570
Ladies, you all agree, right?

681
00:46:24,570 --> 00:46:26,423
Right?

682
00:46:32,210 --> 00:46:34,286
Kyung Mee! Kyung Mee!

683
00:46:34,286 --> 00:46:37,706
You're being too obvious.

684
00:46:37,706 --> 00:46:39,875
What about your friendship with Eun Ok?

685
00:46:39,875 --> 00:46:44,541
Geez, you have no idea.
I'm trying to survive, myself.

686
00:46:45,476 --> 00:46:47,760
If only my husband were better...

687
00:46:48,501 --> 00:46:51,681
Did Manager Change get in trouble again?

688
00:46:51,681 --> 00:46:53,864
It's not like that.

689
00:46:54,547 --> 00:46:58,849
I'm just saying life is hard...

690
00:46:58,849 --> 00:47:00,233
Bye.

691
00:47:00,233 --> 00:47:01,413
Okay.

692
00:47:01,413 --> 00:47:06,106
Okay, what you said was
really intriguing to me too.

693
00:47:06,106 --> 00:47:08,458
But can you keep all of your promises?

694
00:47:08,458 --> 00:47:13,043
You won't be able to do those
things without the chairman's help.

695
00:47:13,043 --> 00:47:16,398
I don't need him. I have Director Baek.

696
00:47:16,398 --> 00:47:17,894
Hey, Lee Do Kyung!

697
00:47:17,894 --> 00:47:22,106
It was just yesterday when we
shook hands on a clean election!

698
00:47:22,106 --> 00:47:24,268
Do you really need to
involve your ex-husband?

699
00:47:24,268 --> 00:47:27,327
Eun Ok, you're being old-fashioned.

700
00:47:27,327 --> 00:47:30,505
Did I cheat? Did I speak badly about you?

701
00:47:30,505 --> 00:47:33,155
In an election, I can use anyone
who will help me to win voters.

702
00:47:33,155 --> 00:47:36,005
That's how elections work.

703
00:47:37,202 --> 00:47:40,268
Fair play, okay?

704
00:47:58,925 --> 00:48:00,179
Thank you.

705
00:48:00,179 --> 00:48:03,900
I told you I didn't feel like eating.

706
00:48:03,900 --> 00:48:08,099
You need to eat when it's time to eat,
even if you don't feel like it.

707
00:48:08,099 --> 00:48:09,581
Okay.

708
00:48:17,315 --> 00:48:19,309
Please sit here.

709
00:48:20,273 --> 00:48:22,911
Okay, sit right here.

710
00:48:30,385 --> 00:48:32,684
Did you wait long?

711
00:48:33,166 --> 00:48:34,731
Are you hungry?

712
00:48:34,731 --> 00:48:37,110
I already ordered.

713
00:48:37,110 --> 00:48:40,605
The one with
lots of cheese, your favorite.

714
00:48:40,605 --> 00:48:45,257
Oh, man! My son knows his manners!

715
00:48:45,257 --> 00:48:47,449
See how sweet he is to you?

716
00:48:49,358 --> 00:48:52,141
Let's eat. The food is getting cold.

717
00:48:56,047 --> 00:49:01,067
In my opinion, I am the only one in
our family who needs to do better.

718
00:49:02,032 --> 00:49:04,141
Everyone else is doing a good job.

719
00:49:04,141 --> 00:49:08,110
Sung Min is good... you are good...

720
00:49:08,110 --> 00:49:09,842
Just forget my mom.

721
00:49:10,827 --> 00:49:15,552
And Soo Min will do better
when she gets older.

722
00:49:16,829 --> 00:49:19,264
Oh, my! I forgot.

723
00:49:19,264 --> 00:49:21,842
It's time to go pick up Soo Min.

724
00:49:21,842 --> 00:49:27,554
Well... enjoy your date
with your son, okay?

725
00:49:29,583 --> 00:49:31,137
I will be back soon.

726
00:49:48,137 --> 00:49:53,199
I am sorry for having
disappointed you and Dad.

727
00:49:53,199 --> 00:49:57,000
I'm sorry I didn't tell
you about me doing music.

728
00:49:57,000 --> 00:50:01,400
I will study hard
during my last year as you wish.

729
00:50:01,400 --> 00:50:04,282
I'll study hard for my goal.

730
00:50:06,146 --> 00:50:07,836
Sung Min!

731
00:50:09,693 --> 00:50:13,844
You made the right decision!
You are my son, indeed!

732
00:50:13,893 --> 00:50:15,807
In return...

733
00:50:17,458 --> 00:50:19,418
I want to major in music composition.

734
00:50:19,418 --> 00:50:20,690
What?

735
00:50:20,690 --> 00:50:24,791
I will go to Seoul University as
you wish, but as a music major.

736
00:50:24,791 --> 00:50:26,632
Are you crazy?

737
00:50:29,739 --> 00:50:32,777
Music can be your hobby!

738
00:50:32,777 --> 00:50:35,965
After you get a good job and
make loads of money, buy a nice guitar!

739
00:50:35,965 --> 00:50:39,103
You can do whatever you want.
I won't stop you then!

740
00:50:39,103 --> 00:50:41,014
Mom...

741
00:50:43,175 --> 00:50:44,815
I am serious.

742
00:50:46,389 --> 00:50:48,722
This is the best scenario,
for both you and me.

743
00:50:48,722 --> 00:50:50,719
Sung Min...

744
00:50:50,719 --> 00:50:55,324
Think about your dad,
who loves you so dearly.

745
00:50:55,324 --> 00:50:57,811
So he can be proud of raising you.

746
00:50:57,811 --> 00:51:00,050
So he can be proud of you.

747
00:51:00,664 --> 00:51:06,177
Dad said... he would support me
no matter what I choose to do.

748
00:51:16,355 --> 00:51:17,833
Dad!

749
00:51:17,833 --> 00:51:19,367
Are you done?

750
00:51:19,367 --> 00:51:21,612
- Bye.
- Bye.

751
00:51:21,682 --> 00:51:23,952
I'm a bit late. Let's go.

752
00:51:26,356 --> 00:51:29,871
Man, kids have hard
lives these days, right?

753
00:51:29,871 --> 00:51:33,541
They study until this late, and then
do homework when they get home.

754
00:51:33,541 --> 00:51:35,481
You're right.

755
00:51:35,481 --> 00:51:41,199
When we were little, we would just
play baseball and run around.

756
00:51:41,849 --> 00:51:46,730
Yes, it was good back then.

757
00:51:47,702 --> 00:51:50,193
Do you like baseball?

758
00:51:50,193 --> 00:51:51,992
Baseball?

759
00:51:51,992 --> 00:51:54,389
I'm sick and tired of it.

760
00:51:56,182 --> 00:51:57,692
Dad!

761
00:51:57,692 --> 00:51:59,556
Hey!

762
00:51:59,556 --> 00:52:03,505
- I told you to speak English!
- Okay.

763
00:52:03,505 --> 00:52:05,844
How was your class today?

764
00:52:05,844 --> 00:52:08,559
Grammar was a bit difficult.

765
00:52:08,559 --> 00:52:09,967
- Really?
- Yes.

766
00:52:09,967 --> 00:52:14,170
Don't worry. I will teach you
some grammar when we get home.

767
00:52:14,170 --> 00:52:16,159
- Okay.
- Okay?

768
00:52:16,159 --> 00:52:19,289
How many words did you memorize?

769
00:52:22,719 --> 00:52:25,675
What a bunch of bullshit.

770
00:52:25,675 --> 00:52:28,813
Hey! Hey!

771
00:52:30,851 --> 00:52:34,565
Hey, come on, baby! Come on!

772
00:52:34,565 --> 00:52:37,023
Come on, baby!

773
00:52:37,023 --> 00:52:39,440
Baby, come on!

774
00:52:39,440 --> 00:52:41,039
What's wrong with him?

775
00:52:41,039 --> 00:52:43,557
Ms. Yoon! Ms. Yoon!

776
00:52:43,557 --> 00:52:45,822
Ms. Yoon! Hey!

777
00:52:46,539 --> 00:52:50,094
Hey! Come on! Come on!

778
00:52:57,695 --> 00:53:01,547
I was so embarrassed that
I couldn't take this out at cram school.

779
00:53:01,547 --> 00:53:04,117
Look at this, Dad.

780
00:53:04,117 --> 00:53:07,695
Mom didn't even apologize to me.
Does that make sense?

781
00:53:07,695 --> 00:53:10,188
I know. Just let it go.

782
00:53:10,188 --> 00:53:13,771
I have the worst phone
in the whole school.

783
00:53:13,771 --> 00:53:17,190
My friends have the newest phones,
while mine has a broken screen!

784
00:53:17,190 --> 00:53:20,547
It's super slow and the
touch screen doesn't work.

785
00:53:20,547 --> 00:53:22,431
What should I do, Dad?

786
00:53:25,717 --> 00:53:27,186
What's wrong?

787
00:53:36,429 --> 00:53:37,838
Welcome!

788
00:53:39,126 --> 00:53:43,030
Sit down here and have some chicken.
I'll be right back.

789
00:53:43,030 --> 00:53:44,516
But I'm not hungry.

790
00:53:44,516 --> 00:53:46,554
Well, I want to have some.

791
00:53:46,554 --> 00:53:48,804
Don't come out at any cost.

792
00:53:48,804 --> 00:53:51,797
If I don't come back within
20 minutes, call your mom.

793
00:53:51,797 --> 00:53:53,199
Okay.

794
00:54:18,000 --> 00:54:21,155
Who the heck are you?
What is this about?

795
00:54:55,590 --> 00:54:57,965
My touch screen...

796
00:54:57,965 --> 00:55:01,018
My cell phone...

797
00:55:15,217 --> 00:55:18,617
<i>[Keep us safe today.]</i>

798
00:55:23,257 --> 00:55:25,719
My goodness!

799
00:55:26,768 --> 00:55:28,168
Geez.

800
00:55:33,753 --> 00:55:35,110
Hey, kid.

801
00:55:38,684 --> 00:55:42,128
He followed me from Soo Min's
cram school last night.

802
00:55:42,128 --> 00:55:45,922
Boss, I dug into Manager Ma.

803
00:55:45,922 --> 00:55:48,813
Sounds like the chairman called
the guys from Cheongjoo.

804
00:55:48,813 --> 00:55:51,610
What? Cheongjoo?

805
00:55:51,610 --> 00:55:55,387
Yes, what would he call them here for?

806
00:55:55,387 --> 00:55:59,597
He would always call us,
dirty work or clean work.

807
00:56:00,978 --> 00:56:05,800
Boss, I'm a bit suspicious
of the chairman.

808
00:56:05,800 --> 00:56:11,559
If it's really those guys,
you never know what they'll do.

809
00:56:16,280 --> 00:56:17,797
This is Yoon Tae Soo.

810
00:56:17,797 --> 00:56:21,425
<i>I'm calling from Soo Min's cram school.
Her mom isn't answering her phone.</i>

811
00:56:21,425 --> 00:56:23,202
<i>Did Soo Min come home?</i>

812
00:56:23,202 --> 00:56:24,867
What do you mean?

813
00:56:37,862 --> 00:56:39,527
What happened to that?

814
00:56:39,527 --> 00:56:43,351
That's my question.
How did that happen?

815
00:56:43,351 --> 00:56:45,003
I don't know!

816
00:56:45,003 --> 00:56:47,858
It was already like that
when we came in.

817
00:56:47,858 --> 00:56:52,034
Geez, when I saw that...

818
00:56:52,034 --> 00:56:54,612
My heart is still beating so hard.

819
00:56:54,612 --> 00:56:57,657
Are you okay, Madam?
Should I get you some medicine?

820
00:57:00,054 --> 00:57:03,199
Please be honest, Eun Ok.

821
00:57:03,199 --> 00:57:06,914
Did you want to win that much?

822
00:57:06,914 --> 00:57:10,257
What are you talking about?
I really don't know anything.

823
00:57:10,257 --> 00:57:12,340
Madam, please stop.

824
00:57:12,340 --> 00:57:14,989
I don't want others to find out.
It's embarrassing.

825
00:57:14,989 --> 00:57:20,396
I'm in charge of the election.
I'm the most embarrassed one here.

826
00:57:21,121 --> 00:57:24,949
Not only the election, but also
One Heart has been disgraced.

827
00:57:24,949 --> 00:57:28,655
Madam, what evidence do
you have against me?

828
00:57:28,655 --> 00:57:32,452
Who else is there that would
do something like this?

829
00:57:36,143 --> 00:57:37,737
Your phone is ringing.

830
00:57:40,592 --> 00:57:42,445
I'm sorry, Honey--

831
00:57:43,492 --> 00:57:44,918
What?

832
00:57:45,548 --> 00:57:47,668
What is it now, Eun Ok?

833
00:57:50,043 --> 00:57:51,936
I have to go now.

834
00:57:51,936 --> 00:57:55,913
Explain it before you go.
Otherwise you're admitting you did this.

835
00:57:55,913 --> 00:57:57,987
I have to go.

836
00:57:58,764 --> 00:58:01,005
What happened to Soo Min?

837
00:58:01,005 --> 00:58:04,657
She was going to see a movie
with a friend after cram school.

838
00:58:04,657 --> 00:58:08,056
But she didn't come
and we can't reach her.

839
00:58:08,056 --> 00:58:09,550
What?

840
00:58:09,550 --> 00:58:15,373
Sung Min's thing was only a few days ago.
Now what's happening?

841
00:58:15,373 --> 00:58:16,634
What about Sung Min?

842
00:58:16,634 --> 00:58:19,467
He went to see Soo Min's friends.

843
00:58:21,811 --> 00:58:23,420
Did you talk to them?

844
00:58:23,943 --> 00:58:28,626
A friend of hers saw her talking
to a man at the bus station.

845
00:58:28,626 --> 00:58:31,963
Man? What kind of man?

846
00:58:31,963 --> 00:58:33,599
Calm down.

847
00:58:33,599 --> 00:58:37,416
Honey, could it be those guys?

848
00:58:40,083 --> 00:58:41,643
Soo Min!

849
00:58:41,643 --> 00:58:45,369
Soo Min! Soo Min!

850
00:58:45,369 --> 00:58:48,161
Soo Min! Yoon Soo Min!

851
00:58:48,911 --> 00:58:50,664
Soo Min!

852
00:58:56,630 --> 00:59:01,114
Sorry. I need to report a missing child.
I can't find my child!

853
00:59:01,114 --> 00:59:02,349
Wait a moment.

854
00:59:02,349 --> 00:59:04,326
- What?
- Where was it?

855
00:59:06,153 --> 00:59:07,644
Well...

856
00:59:09,842 --> 00:59:13,967
Excuse me! Please let me
report a missing child.

857
00:59:13,967 --> 00:59:16,882
I can't find her. She's a sixth grader.

858
00:59:16,882 --> 00:59:19,945
Soo Min! Soo Min!

859
00:59:20,603 --> 00:59:21,994
Soo Min!

860
00:59:21,994 --> 00:59:25,911
Soo Min! Soo Min!

861
00:59:26,572 --> 00:59:28,121
Soo Min!

862
00:59:28,121 --> 00:59:30,195
Soo Min!

863
00:59:35,000 --> 00:59:36,269
<i>Tae Soo.</i>

864
00:59:36,269 --> 00:59:40,382
Now that I see you, you sit tall.

865
00:59:40,382 --> 00:59:42,039
You look even taller than I am!

866
00:59:42,039 --> 00:59:44,358
The chairman called
the guys from Cheongjoo.

867
01:00:03,043 --> 01:00:05,063
What brings you here at this hour?

868
01:00:05,762 --> 01:00:09,224
Mr. Chairman, I need to check something.

869
01:00:09,224 --> 01:00:10,650
Check what?

870
01:00:10,650 --> 01:00:14,179
We can't reach Soo Min.

871
01:00:14,179 --> 01:00:15,827
Where did you daughter go?

872
01:00:25,126 --> 01:00:26,802
Mr. Chairman!

873
01:00:26,802 --> 01:00:29,173
Are you questioning me?

874
01:00:30,463 --> 01:00:32,016
Is that why you came here?

875
01:00:39,217 --> 01:00:43,262
Tae Soo, I know you are
desperate for your daughter.

876
01:00:43,262 --> 01:00:46,500
But how can you doubt me?

877
01:00:46,500 --> 01:00:49,918
Your daughter is like
my own granddaughter!

878
01:00:54,335 --> 01:00:55,510
Yeah.

879
01:00:56,594 --> 01:00:59,085
Boss, we found the guy who did it.

880
01:01:16,659 --> 01:01:19,447
Where's Soo Min? Where's my daughter?

881
01:01:19,447 --> 01:01:20,878
How would I know?

882
01:01:20,878 --> 01:01:22,266
You had me followed.

883
01:01:22,266 --> 01:01:23,804
You got the wrong person!

884
01:01:23,804 --> 01:01:25,726
Your guy fessed up.

885
01:01:25,726 --> 01:01:28,273
I really don't know!

886
01:01:34,141 --> 01:01:37,438
How dare you! Where is Soo Min?

887
01:01:37,438 --> 01:01:39,599
I asked you, where is she?

888
01:01:39,599 --> 01:01:41,978
You said I would be full of regret.

889
01:01:41,978 --> 01:01:45,414
Is this what you plotted
with that swindler?

890
01:01:45,414 --> 01:01:49,148
What are you talking about?
Make it easy for me to understand.

891
01:01:49,148 --> 01:01:53,253
Gi Bum, how can you do this to me?

892
01:01:53,253 --> 01:01:58,177
We do dirty work but we also
have a rule we call the bottom line.

893
01:01:58,177 --> 01:02:02,550
That bottom line is to
not touch our families!

894
01:02:02,550 --> 01:02:06,746
You want to know what happens
when you don't follow the rule?

895
01:02:06,746 --> 01:02:10,423
I will show you clearly! You bastards!

896
01:02:17,123 --> 01:02:22,123
Subtitles by DramaFever

897
01:02:37,304 --> 01:02:39,507
<i>[Sweet Savage Family]</i>

898
01:02:39,507 --> 01:02:41,304
<i>He's gone mad!</i>

899
01:02:41,304 --> 01:02:43,829
<i>It's only a matter of time
before Tae Soo gets to us!</i>

900
01:02:43,829 --> 01:02:45,547
<i>He wants us out of this house.</i>

901
01:02:45,547 --> 01:02:48,219
<i>What have you done to me?</i>

902
01:02:48,219 --> 01:02:50,454
<i>Don't be upset. What's done is done.</i>

903
01:02:50,454 --> 01:02:55,264
<i>No matter what, you are my
son and I'm your father.</i>

904
01:02:55,264 --> 01:02:57,168
<i>- What makes you so confident?
- Let's talk.</i>

905
01:02:57,168 --> 01:02:59,226
<i>- Don't touch me.
- Don't say that.</i>

